OL,3,CLast-ditch talks aim to avert London
OL,4,CTube strikes
OL,6,FTalks will be held on Monday in a last-
OL,7,Fditch bid to avert two 24-hour strikes
OL,8,Fon the London Underground.
OL,10,FCommuters face travel chaos as members
OL,11,Fof the Rail, Maritime and Transport
OL,12,Funion plan to walk out on Tuesday and
OL,13,FThursday.
OL,15,FThe dispute is over the voluntary
OL,16,Fintroduction of a four-day working
OL,17,Fweek with condensed hours.
OL,19,FThe conciliation service Acas will be
OL,20,Finvolved on Monday in efforts to reach
OL,21,Fan eleventh-hour agreement.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
