OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780319468
OL,3,CLast-ditch talks aim to avert London
OL,4,CTube strikes
OL,6,FTransport for London branded the move
OL,7,F"disappointing" and urged passengers
OL,8,Fto check before they travel, warning
OL,9,Fof disruption to Tube services during,
OL,10,Fbefore and after the strikes.
OL,12,FTfL's chief operating officer, Claire
OL,13,FMann, said: "We still believe that the
OL,14,Fpoints they have raised can be worked
OL,15,Fout in time, through more detailed
OL,16,Fdiscussions and we are continuing to
OL,17,Ftalk to the union's representatives to
OL,18,Ffind a way to avoid disruption to
OL,19,FLondon."
OL,26,@uD@MOU{D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
